# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SkillBridge — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in real values.
# After exporting from Bolt, every variable below must be set
# before the app will start successfully.
#
# WHERE TO FIND THE VALUES:
#   Supabase Dashboard → your project → Settings → API
#     • Project URL       → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#     • anon public key    → VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#     • service_role key   → SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY  (server-side only!)
#
#   Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials
#     • OAuth 2.0 Client ID     → VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
#     • OAuth 2.0 Client Secret →  configured in Supabase, NOT in .env
#       (see HANDOFF.md § 4 for details)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Supabase (client-side, safe to expose) ──
# Your Supabase project URL, e.g. https://xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=

# Supabase anon/public key — designed to be public; protected by RLS policies
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ── Supabase (server-side only, NEVER expose in client code) ──
# Supabase service role key — bypasses RLS. Only use in edge functions
# or server-side code. NEVER commit to git or bundle in frontend code.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ── Google OAuth (client-side) ──
# Google OAuth 2.0 Client ID — used by the Supabase client to initiate
# Google Sign-In. Safe to expose (it's embedded in the browser anyway).
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
